Rooting out zama zamas ‘at the face’ where Sibanye-Stillwater (Sibanye) has full operational control is the fastest approach to eliminating their destructive presence underground. For this reason, the company allocates millions every year to stopping illegal mining fully in its tracks. CEO Neal Froneman is confident that it can be fully eradicated by the end of 2018 – thanks to the deployment of the latest technologies designed to control and restrict access to working underground shafts.  This article first appeared in Mining Review Africa Issue 7 2018. It will be published online on the 31st July 2018. You can read the full digital magazine here or subscribe here to receive a print copy.